### Can you find the paper with the best title ever? 

This project consists of two parts.
First, you identify a mathematical paper with an exceptionally or memorable title.
Second, you study the content of the selected paper, presenting the necessary background, main results, and their significance. Coxeter's paper is a great suggestion. 

##### References:

* Coxeter, Harold. My graph. Proc. Lond. Math. Soc., III. Ser. 46, 117-136 (1983).

